                                                                                                               CM steps to tackle terror
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee				                                 
	Calcutta, July 9: The chief minister today outlined the steps his government had taken to protect Calcutta from terror strikes.         
	Replying to a question from WBSP legislator Brahmamoy Nanda, Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee said: Some major terror strikes like the attack on the US information centre and the abduction of the Khadim shoe baron took place in the city. Those involved in the crimes were sentenced to life imprisonment. Against this backdrop, we have taken certain measures.        He said a task force had been set up to oversee the citys security. He mentioned some of the other steps taken:      Checks on vehicles at all entry and exit points across the city        Surprise raids in shopping malls, railway stations, bus stands and religious places.  Stringent procedure of issuing passports and mobile phone SIM cards.                                                                                                                                                                           
